    "We set τ r = 50 ms and δ = 1 ms so that, for example, the attenuation of the average spiking rate drops by 65% for 50 Hz stimulation:",
    "1e -50• 1 50 +.001 = 0.6501 The third stage is a slow temporal integration stage that converts the rapid spike-events time-course S(t) to a slowly changing 'memory' of previous spike history.",
    "This is computed as a linear convolution of S(t) with an impulse response function G(t):",
    "where * denotes convolution.",
    "G(t) is the impulse response function of an n-stage leaky integrator."
